  "prompt": "What is the difference between active voice and passive voice?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of active voice and passive voice:\n\nActive Voice:\n- The subject of the sentence performs the action\n- The subject comes before the verb\n- Generally clearer and more direct\n- Example: \"The dog chased the ball\"\n\nPassive Voice:\n- The subject receives the action\n- The subject comes after the verb or may be omitted\n- Often less direct and can sound more formal or vague\n- Example: \"The ball was chased by the dog\"\n\nKey differences:\n1. Sentence structure\n2. Who/what is performing the action\n3. Clarity and directness\n4. Emphasis on subject or action\n\nActive voice is usually preferred in most writing because it's more straightforward and concise. Passive voice can be useful in scientific writing or when the action is more important than the actor.\n\nExample comparison:\nActive: \"Scientists discovered a new planet\"\nPassive: \"A new planet was discovered by scientists\"",
